      "id": 5784,
      "name": "Mariusz",
      "username": "mowczar",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/47e85d/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-02-17T13:14:12.706Z",
      "cooked": "<p>This is not exactly what I mean. It\u2019s just that my ass goes numb during a long training session when I sit on the saddle all the time. To remedy this, I have to pick it up from the saddle and to do this without interrupting training / driving I have to turn the pedals while standing. I don\u2019t know how this driving position is named in English, so I\u2019m trying to describe it.<br>\nWhen I do this, the power I generate on the pedals is very high and the trainer does not resist me. As a consequence, I spin the pedals faster and faster until I play my best, despite increasing the gear ratio to the maximum.</p>",
      "post_number": 3,
      "post_type": 1,
