      "id": 5785,
      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2022-02-17T21:39:41.862Z",
      "cooked": "<p>So I think I understand and I still think slope or resistance mode is the solution. You can just click the button to switch to resistance or slope before you stand press the + button at the bottom and when you stand up shift to harder gear.  ERG mode will keep the same power while standing no matter how hard you drive so you can\u2019t get a hard standing workout. Also you might need to shift to bigger gear so your trainer can provide enough resistance.  This is not so easy to explain.  You just have play around. Once you get it perfect manually, you can design workouts that do this automatically.</p>",
