      "created_at": "2022-02-22T02:37:55.298Z",
      "cooked": "<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/alex\">@Alex</a> I think what he means is during a steady state workout, standing up and low power requirement is tough. I\u2019ve made workouts in the past like this (see below): the \u201csprints\u201d just provide high resistance so that during standing/low cadence the knees don\u2019t blow out.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/000e1d7540c81d710c6ff813b712a61a42e9090a.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/000e1d7540c81d710c6ff813b712a61a42e9090a\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/0/000e1d7540c81d710c6ff813b712a61a42e9090a_2_690x290.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"ueXW6l0KHTxRYon3G85UrZTFU\" width=\"690\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/0/000e1d7540c81d710c6ff813b712a61a42e9090a_2_690x290.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/0/000e1d7540c81d710c6ff813b712a61a42e9090a_2_1035x435.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/000e1d7540c81d710c6ff813b712a61a42e9090a.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/0/000e1d7540c81d710c6ff813b712a61a42e9090a_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1199\u00d7504 21 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>",
